posts.caption:
Port Douglas providing the goods! 🌴☀️ Sun, cocktails and absolutely nothing to worry about besides what time to eat dinner.

Bikini is from @midnightco 🖤

Ok ✋ I’m ready for more adventure now.
These days my fitness goals have shifted a lot towards being able to achieve things, instead of being able to look a certain way.
I want my body to take me to the top of Half Dome and Angels Landing.
I want to be able to say, I bloody did that! And to experience the most amazing sights in the world with my body. Knowing that it got me there.
And off the back of that, USA 2019 is officially happening! 🇺🇸 The RV is booked and I’m heading back to the states next year for our biggest roadie adventure yet. And I’m freakin PUMPED!!!! 👊🏜⛺️🚍🏔

Does anyone else’s Starbucks order sound like a science experiment? 😂💁🏻‍♀️ One grande iced caramel macchiato skinny with sugar free vanilla syrup pls and don’t stir it thx 😋☕️ Oh, and Happy Halloween 👻🎃! I’m off to Port Douglas tomorrow for a weekend of R&R and very much looking forward to it 🌴🙏

What’s on your bucket list? 💫

Do you have a list of dreams, goals, or things you’d love to see and achieve?
To me, a bucket list is just another way of setting long term exciting goals. Mine is VERY long but it gives me drive and inspiration to work hard. Every year I pick a couple of things and dedicate myself to them. The list can include ANYTHING from travelling the world to fitness achievements. Whatever your life hopes and dreams are 💛✨ This 👆 was on mine. To snorkel The Great Barrier Reef, and I recently ticked it off 💙🙏 What’s something on your list??

Celebrated my beautiful bestie turning 30 last night 💛🎈One too many Amarettos were had, but I wouldn’t have it any other way, because a couple of nights off #fitness is A-OK 👌 Remember that. Hope you all had a beauty of a weekend! 😘

Woke up thismorning in the DIRTIEST mood of all time. Contemplated eating lollies for breakfast, contemplated selling all my sh*t and moving to Cali. But, sucked it up (after whining a lot), got on with the day and whatddya know.. I’m alive. I survived without lollies for breakfast or going Texas chainsaw massacre.
Moral of the story - a bad day is just a bad day. Not a bad life. Either run the week like the legend you are or let the bad moods run you. Choose wisely... 👊✨

Hey hey 👋 Just me, back on the gram and here to say the biggest possible THANK YOU for all of your support the last week 💛🙏 My family and I are truly and deeply forever grateful.

So now, onwards and upwards. Because with support, positivity and love, we are all unbreakable 👊
Stay strong out there my girls. You can handle anything that’s thrown at you. X

Catfishing you all again with a pic that would make it appear I’m tanned and living it up all smiley in the sun... When in reality I’ve spent the day in bed eating lentil chips watching Netflix and have clocked MAYBE 500 steps on the Apple Watch 😂🤦‍♀️ Hands up if you’ve been sick 4,382 times this year? 🙃🙋🏻‍♀️🤧
Srsly I ate broccoli like twice last month why is my body being like this.... 🙄

Today something weird happened... I ran 2km, WILLINGLY 😂🤷‍♀️
As we know, running isn’t my favourite activity, and I have no idea what came over me but I was all of a sudden motivated to move from my desk for 10 minutes and I chose a run.
Even though I usually hate running, I felt bloody great afterwards. So all I can say to you all, is that if you haven’t moved today yet, go do something! Even if it’s only 10 minutes. Get your heart pumping and you’ll thank yourself later. 👊

PS - throw back pic from Yosemite because it’s much better looking than Melbourne suburbia. 🙏❤️

Probably about time to add another Instagram pose to my book of tricks I think... 😂🤸‍♂️ Fun fact that you may not have known: I used to be a gymnast & a swimmer!
Then I quit sport for a couple years and just ate McDonald’s 🤷‍♀️🍔 #oops BUT then I found my love for fitness again and here we are. 👊

Home in Melbs from my little beach getaway, and getting back into the grind lately has been no easy task 😫 Training has been off, eating has been shockingly unbalanced, work ethic has been low and motivation to get started again was non existent. Then, 4:30am this morning my alarm went off and reminded me its time to cut the sh*t and make an effort. I can feel crap every morning and dread the day or I can seize it.
Don’t wait for a Monday to make change. Do it now 💛👊
